The calling of a group of c.10 individuals in a roosting or potentially nesting wood stand in the center of a pond, with most of the individuals showing its pink-breeding-color in the front of its bill. Although there is also about the same numbers of Black-crowned Night Heron in the same wood stand, but most of the sound heard in this record were given by the Little Egrets. Most calls were between 1,000-3,000Hz, with the wobbling sounds between 1,000-1,800Hz most interesting.
